content.text:
Let me analyze the target structure and provide step-by-step instructions to build it.

Analysis of the Main Target Image:
- The structure has two main sections: a left section with arches and a right section that looks like a gate
- Multiple layers of blocks in different colors (red, blue, yellow, green)
- Total blocks used: approximately 13-14 blocks
- Colors used: red, blue, yellow, green, orange

Let me break down the assembly order:

{
    Step1: Move block with index 11 (yellow horizontal base for right section)
    Step2: Move block with index 7 (red cube for right bottom)
    Step3: Move block with index 4 (blue cube for right bottom)
    Step4: Move block with index 10 (green vertical post for right section)
    Step5: Move block with index 11 (yellow horizontal top piece)
    Step6: Move block with index 1 (red arch piece)
    Step7: Move block with index 1 (red arch piece again)
    Step8: Move block with index 14 (yellow curved piece)
    Step9: Move block with index 14 (yellow curved piece again)
    Step10: Move block with index 4 (blue cube)
    Step11: Move block with index 5 (green cube)
    Step12: Move block with index 12 (yellow vertical piece)
    Step13: Move block with index 12 (yellow vertical piece again)
    Step14: Move block with index 6 (orange cube)
}

This assembly order starts from the base and works up, first completing the right gate-like structure, then building the left section with the arches. The blocks are placed in a logical sequence that ensures stability while building upward.
